casebody.data:
BEN A. ADAMS COMPANY, Inc., Appellant, v. The FORT MITCHELL COUNTRY CLUB, Incorporated, Appellee. No. 7762. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 14, 1937. Rouse & Price, of Covington, Ky., for appellant. William J. Deupree, of Covington, Ky., for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The court having considered the motion of appellee to dismiss the appeal, and appellant’s objections thereto, it is now ordered that the motion to dismiss be, and the same is hereby, granted.

Appeal dismissed.
